<paragraph blockId="2.[148,1488,2020,2128]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
Figs. 7–17. 
<taxonomicName authority="Rédei, 2008" authorityName="Rédei" authorityYear="2008" box="[263,480,2020,2041]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Ploiaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vandoesburgi" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[263,480,2020,2041]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Ploiaria vandoesburgi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[492,611,2020,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male: 7, pygophore, dorsal aspect; 8, same, lateral aspect; 9, superoposterior projection of pygophore, lateral aspect; 10, same, ventral aspect; 11, left paramere, dorsal aspect; 12, same, lateral aspect; 13, phallus, from right; 14, phallosoma, from left; 15, dorsal sclerites of phallosoma, dorsal aspect; 16, articulatory apparatus, anterolateral aspect; 17, same, dorsal aspect. Arrow in Fig. 13 shows the aspect of Fig. 17. Scale bar measurements in mm.
