<paragraph blockId="3.[126,765,206,325]" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">wide whitish annulus apically; mid tibia yellowish with a small dark brown spot at base and with a dark brown annulus apically; tarsus dark brown; apex of femur, tibia and tarsus of hind leg missing.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[126,765,366,677]" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Structure. Body surface and pilosity. Body dull, membranous parts of fore wing slightly shining, iridescent. Head, thorax and abdomen densely covered with rather long, adpressed, pale pubescence; antennal segments I and II with very long and fine pilosity; longest hairs about 8 times as long as diameter of segment I; hairs on segment II gradually shortening towards apex; segments III and IV and apex of segment II with short, semierect pilosity; fore legs with dense, semierect pilosity with longer hairs on dorsal surface of tibia; hind legs with very short and dense, adpressed hairs.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[126,765,718,1157]" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[196,295,718,741]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[126,170,2051,2072]" captionTargetBox="[129,1462,621,2005]" captionTargetId="figure-8@1.[117,1481,603,2019]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 1, head, thorax and fore leg, lateral aspect; 2, head and thorax, dorsal aspect; 3, head, dorsal aspect; 4, trochanter of left fore leg; 5, right fore wing; 6, joint area of pro- and mesosterna, ventral aspect. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354425/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
) relatively short, about 1.15 times as long as width across eyes; anteocular part about 2.2 times as long as postocular; anterior lobe strongly declivent anteriorly, with a short and deep sulcus along meson before interocular furrow; posterior lobe strongly converging posteriorly in dorsal aspect, with a distinct longitudinal ridge; width across eyes about 3 times as wide as interocular distance; eyes very large, globose, reaching ventral outline of head in lateral aspect. Labium almost straight; visible segment III longest, about 1.65 times as long as visible segment II, visible segments I and II subequal in length; apex of visible segment I surpassing antenniferous tubercle, apex of visible segment II slightly surpassing middle of eye. Antenna long and gracile; segment I about 1.15 times as long as segment II.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[126,765,1197,1477]" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">
Thorax. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[341,445,1198,1221]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[126,170,2051,2072]" captionTargetBox="[129,1462,621,2005]" captionTargetId="figure-8@1.[117,1481,603,2019]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 1, head, thorax and fore leg, lateral aspect; 2, head and thorax, dorsal aspect; 3, head, dorsal aspect; 4, trochanter of left fore leg; 5, right fore wing; 6, joint area of pro- and mesosterna, ventral aspect. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354425/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
) about 1.25 times as long as head, about 2.3 times as long as greatest width of anterior lobe; posterior lobe reduced, separated from anterior lobe by wide constriction, widely emarginated posteriorly. Prosternum very narrowly and shallowly excised posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[134,200,1358,1381]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[126,170,2051,2072]" captionTargetBox="[129,1462,621,2005]" captionTargetId="figure-8@1.[117,1481,603,2019]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 1, head, thorax and fore leg, lateral aspect; 2, head and thorax, dorsal aspect; 3, head, dorsal aspect; 4, trochanter of left fore leg; 5, right fore wing; 6, joint area of pro- and mesosterna, ventral aspect. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354425/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum about 1.5 times as long as wide, about 0.95 times as long as pronotum along meson, with a wide, shallow median furrow. Fore wing (
<figureCitation box="[500,561,1422,1445]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[126,170,2051,2072]" captionTargetBox="[129,1462,621,2005]" captionTargetId="figure-8@1.[117,1481,603,2019]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 1, head, thorax and fore leg, lateral aspect; 2, head and thorax, dorsal aspect; 3, head, dorsal aspect; 4, trochanter of left fore leg; 5, right fore wing; 6, joint area of pro- and mesosterna, ventral aspect. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354425/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) reaching posterior margin of tergite VII.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[126,765,1518,2085]" lastBlockId="3.[825,1464,206,261]" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">
Legs. Fore leg as in 
<figureCitation box="[364,432,1518,1541]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[126,170,2051,2072]" captionTargetBox="[129,1462,621,2005]" captionTargetId="figure-8@1.[117,1481,603,2019]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 1, head, thorax and fore leg, lateral aspect; 2, head and thorax, dorsal aspect; 3, head, dorsal aspect; 4, trochanter of left fore leg; 5, right fore wing; 6, joint area of pro- and mesosterna, ventral aspect. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354425/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
; coxa subcylindrical, slightly widening apically; trochanter (
<figureCitation box="[440,501,1550,1573]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[126,170,2051,2072]" captionTargetBox="[129,1462,621,2005]" captionTargetId="figure-8@1.[117,1481,603,2019]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 1, head, thorax and fore leg, lateral aspect; 2, head and thorax, dorsal aspect; 3, head, dorsal aspect; 4, trochanter of left fore leg; 5, right fore wing; 6, joint area of pro- and mesosterna, ventral aspect. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354425/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) with a ventral projection much longer than wide at base and bearing a relatively short apical spine; femur rather long, about 1.6 times as long as coxa, armed ventrally with two series of rather uniform, long and slender spines inserted on very short, wart-like basal processes, intermixed with several shorter spines; spines of both series gradually shortening towards apex of femur; posteroventral series beginning near base of femur, composed of about 30 spiniferous processes; anteroventral series not interrupted at base, composed of about 35 spiniferous processes; tibia about 0.6 times as long as femur, straight, distinctly widened in its apical third, armed with a single series of about 23 long and slender spines inserted on very short, wart-like basal processes; tarsus about half as long as tibia, three-segmented; segment I longest, about 1.6 and 2.3 times as long as segments II and III, respectively; pretarsus with two claws, outer (posterior) claw distinctly shorter than inner (anterior) one. Mid and hind legs elongate and delicate; femora surpassing apex of abdomen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[825,1464,302,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Abdomen slender, about 1.3 times as long as head and thorax taken together, segment VII not projecting posteriorly.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[825,1465,398,837]" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">
Male genitalia. Pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1251,398,421]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[148,192,2020,2041]" captionTargetBox="[158,1482,278,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-85@2.[128,1504,253,1963]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 7–17. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 7, pygophore, dorsal aspect; 8, same, lateral aspect; 9, superoposterior projection of pygophore, lateral aspect; 10, same, ventral aspect; 11, left paramere, dorsal aspect; 12, same, lateral aspect; 13, phallus, from right; 14, phallosoma, from left; 15, dorsal sclerites of phallosoma, dorsal aspect; 16, articulatory apparatus, anterolateral aspect; 17, same, dorsal aspect. Arrow in Fig. 13 shows the aspect of Fig. 17. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354427/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Figs. 7–8</figureCitation>
) elongate, slightly flattened laterally, with a narrow, triangular superoposterior projection (
<figureCitation box="[943,1056,462,485]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[148,192,2020,2041]" captionTargetBox="[158,1482,278,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-85@2.[128,1504,253,1963]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 7–17. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 7, pygophore, dorsal aspect; 8, same, lateral aspect; 9, superoposterior projection of pygophore, lateral aspect; 10, same, ventral aspect; 11, left paramere, dorsal aspect; 12, same, lateral aspect; 13, phallus, from right; 14, phallosoma, from left; 15, dorsal sclerites of phallosoma, dorsal aspect; 16, articulatory apparatus, anterolateral aspect; 17, same, dorsal aspect. Arrow in Fig. 13 shows the aspect of Fig. 17. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354427/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Figs. 9–10</figureCitation>
). Paramere (
<figureCitation box="[1182,1306,462,485]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[148,192,2020,2041]" captionTargetBox="[158,1482,278,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-85@2.[128,1504,253,1963]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 7–17. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 7, pygophore, dorsal aspect; 8, same, lateral aspect; 9, superoposterior projection of pygophore, lateral aspect; 10, same, ventral aspect; 11, left paramere, dorsal aspect; 12, same, lateral aspect; 13, phallus, from right; 14, phallosoma, from left; 15, dorsal sclerites of phallosoma, dorsal aspect; 16, articulatory apparatus, anterolateral aspect; 17, same, dorsal aspect. Arrow in Fig. 13 shows the aspect of Fig. 17. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354427/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Figs. 11–12</figureCitation>
) distinctly bent in dorsal view, apically approaching apex of superoposterior projection of pygophore in resting position (
<figureCitation box="[1299,1365,526,549]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[148,192,2020,2041]" captionTargetBox="[158,1482,278,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-85@2.[128,1504,253,1963]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 7–17. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 7, pygophore, dorsal aspect; 8, same, lateral aspect; 9, superoposterior projection of pygophore, lateral aspect; 10, same, ventral aspect; 11, left paramere, dorsal aspect; 12, same, lateral aspect; 13, phallus, from right; 14, phallosoma, from left; 15, dorsal sclerites of phallosoma, dorsal aspect; 16, articulatory apparatus, anterolateral aspect; 17, same, dorsal aspect. Arrow in Fig. 13 shows the aspect of Fig. 17. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354427/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Phallus (
<figureCitation box="[833,971,558,581]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[148,192,2020,2041]" captionTargetBox="[158,1482,278,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-85@2.[128,1504,253,1963]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 7–17. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 7, pygophore, dorsal aspect; 8, same, lateral aspect; 9, superoposterior projection of pygophore, lateral aspect; 10, same, ventral aspect; 11, left paramere, dorsal aspect; 12, same, lateral aspect; 13, phallus, from right; 14, phallosoma, from left; 15, dorsal sclerites of phallosoma, dorsal aspect; 16, articulatory apparatus, anterolateral aspect; 17, same, dorsal aspect. Arrow in Fig. 13 shows the aspect of Fig. 17. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354427/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Figs. 13–17</figureCitation>
) slightly asymmetrical; phallobase largely membranous; phallosoma elongated, with a plate-like ventral sclerite and two short, asymmetrical, curved dorsal sclerotized processes (
<figureCitation box="[938,1014,654,677]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[148,192,2020,2041]" captionTargetBox="[158,1482,278,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-85@2.[128,1504,253,1963]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 7–17. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 7, pygophore, dorsal aspect; 8, same, lateral aspect; 9, superoposterior projection of pygophore, lateral aspect; 10, same, ventral aspect; 11, left paramere, dorsal aspect; 12, same, lateral aspect; 13, phallus, from right; 14, phallosoma, from left; 15, dorsal sclerites of phallosoma, dorsal aspect; 16, articulatory apparatus, anterolateral aspect; 17, same, dorsal aspect. Arrow in Fig. 13 shows the aspect of Fig. 17. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354427/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); endosoma with numerous small, subequal toothlike processes. Articulatory apparatus connected to phallosoma at considerable distance of its base (
<figureCitation box="[1316,1391,718,741]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[148,192,2020,2041]" captionTargetBox="[158,1482,278,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-85@2.[128,1504,253,1963]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 7–17. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 7, pygophore, dorsal aspect; 8, same, lateral aspect; 9, superoposterior projection of pygophore, lateral aspect; 10, same, ventral aspect; 11, left paramere, dorsal aspect; 12, same, lateral aspect; 13, phallus, from right; 14, phallosoma, from left; 15, dorsal sclerites of phallosoma, dorsal aspect; 16, articulatory apparatus, anterolateral aspect; 17, same, dorsal aspect. Arrow in Fig. 13 shows the aspect of Fig. 17. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354427/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
); basal plates slightly diverging apically (
<figureCitation box="[1213,1297,750,773]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[148,192,2020,2041]" captionTargetBox="[158,1482,278,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-85@2.[128,1504,253,1963]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 7–17. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 7, pygophore, dorsal aspect; 8, same, lateral aspect; 9, superoposterior projection of pygophore, lateral aspect; 10, same, ventral aspect; 11, left paramere, dorsal aspect; 12, same, lateral aspect; 13, phallus, from right; 14, phallosoma, from left; 15, dorsal sclerites of phallosoma, dorsal aspect; 16, articulatory apparatus, anterolateral aspect; 17, same, dorsal aspect. Arrow in Fig. 13 shows the aspect of Fig. 17. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354427/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
), connected to phallosoma with a long, paired basal plate extension (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[148,192,2020,2041]" captionTargetBox="[158,1482,278,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-85@2.[128,1504,253,1963]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 7–17. Ploiaria vandoesburgi, new species, male: 7, pygophore, dorsal aspect; 8, same, lateral aspect; 9, superoposterior projection of pygophore, lateral aspect; 10, same, ventral aspect; 11, left paramere, dorsal aspect; 12, same, lateral aspect; 13, phallus, from right; 14, phallosoma, from left; 15, dorsal sclerites of phallosoma, dorsal aspect; 16, articulatory apparatus, anterolateral aspect; 17, same, dorsal aspect. Arrow in Fig. 13 shows the aspect of Fig. 17. Scale bar measurements in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354427/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[825,1465,877,1285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis box="[825,1106,877,901]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[825,986,877,901]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Measurements</emphasis>
